snippet: Kaillie Humphries of Canada finished sixth, and Elana Meyers Taylor of the United States was seventh, becoming the first women to drive against men in an international four-man bobsled competition.
abstract: Olympic champion Kaillie Humphries of Canada finishes sixth, and Olympic silver medalist Elana Meyers Taylor of United States is seventh, becoming first women to drive against men in an international four-man bobsled competition.
lead_paragraph: Kaillie Humphries of Canada finished sixth, and Elana Meyers Taylor of the United States was seventh, becoming the first women to drive against men in an international four-man bobsled competition.

headline.main: Women Make 4-Man Bobsled History in Utah
